bazaar /bəˈzɑː/

(bazaars) 

1. N-COUNT In areas such as the Middle East and India, a bazaar is a place where there are many small stores and stalls. (中东、印度等地的) 集市 

例： Kamal was a vendor in Cairo's open-air bazaar. 卡莫尔曾是开罗露天集市的摊贩。 

2. N-COUNT A bazaar is a sale to raise money for charity. 义卖会 

例： ...a church bazaar. …一场教会义卖会。

